name: Adinkra Wine Charms
description:
This is a beautiful 6-piece assortment of pewter Adinkra wine glass charms made with semi-precious gemstone beads, and silver plated wine glass stem rings. 

The gemstones used in these charms include: smoky quartz, amethyst, rose quartz, rock crystal quartz, carnelian and amazonite. 

The average measurement of the finished charm is approximately 28 x 14mm, give or take a bit. They are perfect for any standard sized wine glass. The circular loop opens easily and fastens securely.

I find that these charms make wonderful favors for a special party or event, a nice little gift for a hostess, or just the "best of the best" of wine glass charms for your own very special dinner party!

name: Adinkra Earrings- 5 Styles
description:
Adinkra symbols were first used as decorative elements in some of the most highly valued, hand printed and hand embroidered cloths called Adinkra. Its origin is traced to the Asante people of Ghana and the Gyaman people of CÃ´te d'Ivoire (Ivory Coast). The production and use of Adinkra Symbols have come to be more associated with the Asante people than any other group of people. 

In modern times, Adinkra cloths are used for a wide range of social activities. In addition to its sacred usage, it is also used to make clothing for such special occasions  as festivals, churchgoing, weddings, naming ceremonies and initiation rites. Today, designers use Adinkra symbols in creating a wide range of products including clothing  accessories, interior decoration, packages and book covers.

Each of the motifs that make up the collection of Adinkra symbols has a name and meaning derived either from a proverb, a historical event, human attitude, animal behavior, plant life, forms and shapes  of inanimate and man-made objects. These are graphically rendered in stylized geometric shapes  and meanings of motifs may be categorized as follows: Aesthetics, Ethics, Human Relations and Religious  concepts. 

In its totality, Adinkra symbolism is a visual representation of social thought relating to the history, philosophy and religious beliefs of the Akan people of Ghana and CÃ´te d'Ivoire.

IMPORTANT!!! 
When ordering more then one pair of earrings please specify which earrings you are ordering in the "note to seller" section during checkout.

Bora takes a new twist on a classic accessory with its innovative interpretation of the infinity scarf.

Multiple wool strands are gathered together for a simple, elegant look available in a variety of bold, bright hues. Whether worn loose and long like a necklace or twisted and twice around for a more snug and cozy fit, Aria scarves drape and hang with ease and beauty thanks to a unique blend of alpaca and acrylic.

Despite what appears to be a rather simple design, Bora scarves are actually quite difficult to make. Each scarf is handcrafted in North Carolina and sourced from local farms in the Asheville region. The alpaca wool is prickle-free, hypo-allergenic, soft, durable, and water repellent.

Bora Scarves add a splash of color and unique style to any outfit or coat--the perfect statement piece and cold-weather accessory all wrapped into one.
